            <h3>Introduction</h3>
            Please read these Terms and Conditions carefully. The terms “We” / “Us” / “Our”/”Company” individually and collectively refer to Bvend Technologies Ltd. while the term “User” refers to the people who will purchase products from the vending machines and the term “Vendor” refers to the people who will own vending machines from Bvend Technologies Ltd. to sell their products. 
            Bvend mobile application is designed to be accessed and used by anyone willing to purchase products from our vending machines. It does not provide business management services to Vendors; for which we have a separate online platform.
            <h3>Acceptance and Usage of the application</h3>
            Each “User” is required to agree to and comply with these terms and conditions before they continue to use the services offered on this application. If a User disagrees with any part of these terms and conditions, they may discontinue using and/or access the application and/or the Services. By installing and using our services User agrees to the Terms and Conditions mentioned on this application and acknowledges to be bound by the present and future updates of the Terms and Conditions. Any amendments and additions to the Terms and Conditions will be effective upon posting of an updated version of the Bvend app as well as notices on our website. We encourage our Users and Vendors to check our application and visit our website on a regular basis. Because once posted changes to Terms and Conditions will be effective and whether or not reviewed by Users will be considered to have their consent and acceptance. By accessing/using this application User agrees to be solely responsible for consequences resulted from any breach of these Terms and Conditions. The application should be accessed/used only for the purposes mentioned in (i) these terms and conditions and (ii) guidelines or instructions from Bvend Technologies Ltd.
            <h3>Services</h3>
            We are a technology company and we provide our service by creating a cashless business platform between users and vendors with the help of our system. However, our intention to connect vendors with users should not be deemed as an act of product supply. The vendors are only using our system to reach their product to the users and users are using our system to purchase products from the vendors. By agreeing to our Terms and Conditions a User understands and accepts that Bvend Technologies Ltd. is not a product supplier. 
            <h3>Information Collected</h3>
            To install and continue to access/use the application, a User needs to provide 1) phone number 2) Bkash account number to use our mobile payment service. Please ensure the information provided is accurate and updated. 
            Bkash payment system is our only payment method for now. Only those who have registered Bkash accounts can use our services. Bkash does not share your account information with us. The information you share with Bkash during registration is also not disclosed to us or stored in our system in any form. 
            <h3>How we use your information</h3>
            When a User signs up with a phone number we use it to send one time password, to keep log of the User and to assist with payments. We use transaction records to understand Users’ purchase behavior and share them with our Vendor upon User’s consent. 
            <h3>User Guideline</h3>
            By agreeing to our Terms and Conditions User further confirms that:
            <ul>
                <li>A User shall only use authorized means to access/use our service.</li>
                <li>A User should use a compatible device and download the correct version of the application.</li>
                <li>A User will only use our service for purposes acceptable by our guidelines and the law of Bangladesh.</li>
                <li>A User will not use the application to attempt a forgery or purchase products that are considered illegal.</li>
                <li>A User confirms to be responsible for proper handling of the vending machines during product purchase.</li>
                <li>A User should not attempt to collect the products from the vending machines in ways outside instructed, shown and advertised on the surface of the machines, on our website and social media platforms.</li>
                <li>A User will only provide correct, updated, and true information. In case of submission of incorrect, un-updated and untrue information we hold the rights to suspend or terminate your account and refuse any/all current and future use of our services.</li>
                <li>A User will not share their Bkash account pin with anyone at any cost. More information on Bkash account security can be found in bkash.com.</li>
                <li>A user will not make improper use of our support service, report/ submit claims for false allegations.</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Payment & Refund Policy</h3>
            Bkash mobile payment system is our only payment method for now. A user must have a registered Bkash account to use our service. We will not store or collect Bkash account details. We will only keep records of the number of transactions done on our application in order to understand consumption behavior of Users. 
            Bkash privacy policy can be viewed here Bkash.com
            A User can report unsuccessful transactions upon payment, product quality issues, and other concerns using our support service. Our support service works relentlessly to make sure a User report is addressed within 48hours. After careful discretion, A user will receive a full refund for cases of unsuccessful transactions. 
